In terms of applications, packaging continues to be the dominant segment for PVA films, fueled by the need for moisture resistance, biodegradability, and efficient barrier properties in packaging materials. The textiles, construction, electronics, and other sectors also contribute to the market growth with unique requirements for PVA films in their respective applications. The electronics industry, in particular, is witnessing a surge in demand for polarizer PVA films, driven by the expanding consumer electronics market and the need for high-quality display technologies.

The end-use industry segmentation further highlights the significance of PVA films in varied sectors such as food packaging, pharmaceuticals, agriculture, and construction. The food packaging industry stands out as a key end-user of PVA films due to regulatory requirements and the emphasis on sustainable packaging solutions. Pharmaceutical companies also rely on PVA films for their solvent resistance and stability, ensuring product integrity and safety during packaging and transportation processes.

